title: Kurt Vile tops bestsellers at Jupiter Records
text:
Facebook Email Twitter Google+ LinkedIn Pinterest Kurt Vile tops bestsellers at Jupiter Records After topping the charts at Rainbow Records last week, Philadelphia's Kurt Vile is back on top at Jupiter Records. Join the Conversation Ryan Cormier , The News Journal 12:41 p.m. EDT October 21, 2015 
Kurt Vile's "b'lieve i'm goin deep down..." (Photo: Matador Records) 
Each week, Rainbow Records (54 E. Main St., Newark, [302] 368-7738) or Jupiter Records (2200 Marsh Road, near Arden, [302] 475-3209) provides a list of the top-selling albums from the past week, giving a glimpse of customers' preferences. This week's list is from Jupiter Records. 
1. Kurt Vile, "b'lieve i'm goin (deep) down..." 
2. Beach House, "Depression Cherry" 
3. Beirut, "No No No" 
4. of Montreal, "Snare Lustrous Doomings" 
5. Destroyer, "Poison Season" 
6. Mac Demarco, "Another One" 
7. Tame Impala, "Currents" 
9. La Luz, "Weirdo Shrine" 
10. The Front Bottoms, "Back on Top"
